title: Diet Pepsi

description.plain:
Rumoured to be on Addison Rae’s upcoming project, “Diet Pepsi” stands as the first single after the release of her debut EP, AR, and marks the beginning of a new era for her discography after her collaboration with hyperpop icon Charli xcx on the remixed rendition of “Von Dutch”.

A track infused with motifs familiar to that of Lana Del Rey’s fifth studio album, Lust For Life; the lyrics seemingly allude to the teenage love-filled zeitgeist of the 70s, a fact only further enforced by the lustful escapades mentioned throughout the song.

The cover also elicits the Americana culture of the era, with Levi Jeans and the eponymous “Diet Pepsi” being almost iconographical of this period, a concept also not unfamiliar to that of Lana too.
